# Technical SEO Checklist

Essential technical SEO elements for modern web applications.

## Metadata

### Title Tags

- Unique per page <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- 50-60 characters <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Primary keyword near the beginning <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Brand name at the end (optional) <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->

### Meta Descriptions

- Unique per page <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- 150-160 characters <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Include call-to-action <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Contain relevant keywords <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->

### Open Graph

```html
<meta property="og:title" content="Page Title" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Description" />
<meta property="og:image" content="https://example.com/image.jpg" />
<meta property="og:url" content="https://example.com/page" />
<meta property="og:type" content="article" />
```

### Sanity + Next.js Implementation

```typescript
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const { data } = await sanityFetch({
    query: PAGE_QUERY,
    stega: false,  // Critical: no stega in metadata
  })
  
  return {
    title: data.seo?.title || data.title,
    description: data.seo?.description,
    openGraph: {
      images: data.seo?.image ? [{
        url: urlFor(data.seo.image).width(1200).height(630).url(),
        width: 1200,
        height: 630,
      }] : [],
    },
    robots: data.seo?.noIndex ? 'noindex' : undefined,
  }
}
```

## Sitemaps

Dynamic sitemap from CMS content:

```typescript
// app/sitemap.ts
import { MetadataRoute } from 'next'

export default async function sitemap(): Promise<MetadataRoute.Sitemap> {
  const pages = await client.fetch(`
    *[_type in ["page", "post"] && defined(slug.current) && seo.noIndex != true]{
      "url": select(
        _type == "page" => "/" + slug.current,
        _type == "post" => "/blog/" + slug.current
      ),
      _updatedAt
    }
  `)
  
  return pages.map(page => ({
    url: `https://example.com${page.url}`,
    lastModified: new Date(page._updatedAt),
    changeFrequency: 'weekly',
    priority: 0.8,
  }))
}
```

## Canonical URLs

Prevent duplicate content issues:

```typescript
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    alternates: {
      canonical: `https://example.com/${params.slug}`,
    },
  }
}
```

## Redirects

CMS-managed redirects:

```typescript
// next.config.ts
async redirects() {
  const redirects = await client.fetch(`
    *[_type == "redirect" && isEnabled == true]{
      source,
      destination,
      permanent
    }
  `)
  return redirects
}
```

## Performance

[Core Web Vitals](https://web.dev/articles/defining-core-web-vitals-thresholds) impact rankings:

- **LCP (Largest Contentful Paint):** < 2.5s <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- **INP (Interaction to Next Paint):** < 200ms <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- **CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift):** < 0.1 <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->

### Image Optimization (Next.js example)

- Use `next/image` with Sanity URL builder <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Serve WebP/AVIF formats <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Implement LQIP blur placeholders <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->
- Set explicit dimensions <!-- decay:2026-03-17 tier:cold rel:0.28 -->

### Font Loading (Next.js example)

```typescript
// Prevent layout shift
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google'
const inter = Inter({ subsets: ['latin'], display: 'swap' })
```

## Robots.txt

```
# public/robots.txt
User-agent: *
Allow: /
Disallow: /api/
Disallow: /studio/

Sitemap: https://example.com/sitemap.xml
```

## Distilled 2026-03-24

### Image Carousel SERP — Optimization Layers

- SERP image carousel eligibility depends on multiple independent signals — tackle in sequence: <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
  1. **Schema markup** — `ImageObject` with `contentUrl`, `description`, `thumbnail` (highest leverage, do first)
  2. **Volume** — minimum ~8–10 indexed images per page/gallery recommended
  3. **Metadata quality** — `alt` text descriptive and keyword-relevant, `title` attribute populated
  4. **Re-indexing** — submit via IndexNow + Google Search Console after all above are in place
- **Diagnostic approach**: if carousel absent after schema, check Coverage report for indexation status before assuming metadata problem. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

## Distilled 2026-03-26

### CWV — Live Site Readings (studiokook.ee, 2026-03-25)

- **LCP**: 2.1s ✅ good (threshold <2.5s) <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->
- **INP**: 180ms ⚠️ needs improvement (threshold <200ms — close to boundary, monitor) <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->
- **CLS**: 0.05 ✅ good (threshold <0.1) <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->
- Source: SEO Audit Weekly 2026-03-25 <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->

### Image Optimization Gotcha — Missing Explicit Dimensions

- Images without `width`/`height` attributes cause CLS even when file is optimized <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->
- **Detected**: /koogid page — 3 images missing width/height <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->
- Fix: always set explicit dimensions on `<img>` tags (or `next/image` equivalent); prevents layout shift before image loads <!-- decay:2026-03-26 tier:cold rel:0.415 -->

## Distilled 2026-04-25 (from troubleshooting-current + global-patterns)

### Schema & Structured Data

- **GOTCHA: robots.txt blocking JS/CSS** — `Disallow: /wp-content/plugins/` prevents Googlebot rendering. Managed via mu-plugin hooking `do_robotstxt` at `PHP_INT_MAX` priority with `exit` before `apply_filters`.
- **GOTCHA: BreadcrumbList without @id** — Yoast WebPage references `#breadcrumb` but BreadcrumbList lacks `@id`, causing Google to see two entities. Fix: add `@id` to BreadcrumbList; remove conflicting `breadcrumb` reference from Yoast WebPage rather than relying on `@id` auto-merging.
- **GOTCHA: Existing plugin overriding robots.txt** — fix: use `do_robotstxt` action with `PHP_INT_MAX` priority and `exit` to ensure new logic takes precedence.
- **GOTCHA: Product Schema generated by post_meta (snippet 102), not Yoast** — mu-plugin must update `post_meta` directly and filter snippet 102 output, not just add new JSON-LD.
- **GOTCHA: Product schema missing required fields** — HPL page lacked `image`, `offers` (price/priceCurrency), `review`, `aggregateRating`. Fix: draft mu-plugin `sk-pages-product-enricher.php`.
- **GOTCHA: Avoid unconfirmed brand names in schema** — do not inject Technistone/Caesarstone; use confirmed manufacturer (Studioköök OÜ) to avoid Google spam policy violation.

### Caching & Indexation

- **GOTCHA: Seraphinite static cache served stale HTML** — Google fetched old version from CDN edge despite local verify showing clean HTML. Fix: POST empty meta update on affected posts to trigger `save_post` and invalidate Seraphinite cache.
- **GOTCHA: Google Rich Results Test caches old results** — force fresh fetch by adding unique cache-bust parameter to URL (e.g., `?v=timestamp`) or clicking 'Test live URL' in RRT.
- **GOTCHA: `wpseo_schema_webpage` filter scoped too narrowly** — limiting filter to `is_singular('sk_portfolio')` leaves regular pages without the BreadcrumbList fix ('Отсутствует поле itemListElement'). Fix: extend filter condition to `is_page() || is_singular()` to cover all pages. Apply the same broad scope to any Product schema patches.


